Package: ergm.tapered
Type: Package
Title: Tapered ERGMs for Network Modeling
Version: 1.0-5
Date: 2018-02-22
Authors@R: c(
	  person("Pavel N.", "Krivitsky", role=c("aut","cre"), email="pavel@uow.edu.au"),
	  person("Ian", "Fellows", role=c("aut"), email="ian@fellstat.com"),
	  person("Mark S.", "Handcock", role=c("aut"), email="handcock@stat.ucla.edu"))
Description: A set of terms and functions implementing Tapered ERGMs. Tapered
    ERGMs are a modification to ERGMs that reduce the effects of phase transitions,
    and with properly chosen hyper-parameters, provably removes all multiphase
    behavior.
BugReports: https://github.com/statnet/ergm.tapered/issues
LinkingTo: ergm
Depends:
    ergm (>= 4.0),
    network
Imports:
    statnet.common (>= 4.1)
License: GPL-3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
